<div class='toload proposition'>
<p><span class='envidentifier'>Proposition 1.8.16</span>
If $\G$ is an ample Hausdorff groupoid and $S=\KB(\G)$, then $S$ satisfies condition (SC) if and only if $\G$ is $\sigma$-compact. More precisely, a subset $C\subseteq\KB(\G)$ satisfies (SC1)-(SC2) if and only if $\G\subseteq\bigcup C$.
</p>
